NAME
        udefrag - manual page for udefrag

SYNOPSIS
        udefrag [OPTION]...

DESCRIPTION
        'udefrag' lists, analyzes, defragments and optimizes drives.
        The default action is to defragment the supplied drives.

OPTIONS
        -l
                list all available drives excluding removeable ones
                can not be used with any other option
        
        -la
                list all available drives including removeable ones
                can not be used with any other option
        
        -a
                only analyze the drives
                can not be used with the '-o' option
        
        -o
                optimize the drives
                can not be used with the '-a' option
        
        {drive letter}:
                one or more drives separated by spaces
                can be omited if one of the --all... options is used

        --all
                perform action for all available drives including
                removeable ones
        
        --all-fixed
                Perform action for all available drives excluding
                removeable ones
                If the '--all' option is specified too, this option
                takes precedance

EXAMPLES
        udefrag C:
                Defragment drive C:
        
        udefrag -la
                List all available drives
        
        udefrag -a --all-fixed
                Analyze all drives excluding removeable ones
        
        udefrag E: K: -o
                optimize drives E: and K:

